The Office administration intimates, motivates, guides and assists students in applying for any applicable scholarships/financial aid. The Office also performs correspondence between the Institute and Government agencies. A few of the scholarships under the umbrella of the Institute are as follows:-
a.	SC scholarship for Top Class students
b.	ST scholarship for Top Class students
c.	Fee remission to EWS B.Tech. students
d. 	 UGC-CSIR JRF/SRF funding

“Good Art Inspires, Good design Motivates”

“One of the only ways to get out of a tight box is to invent your way out.” 
~Jeff Bezos

Here at E-cell - The Entrepreneurship Cell of IIT Jodhpur, we aim to help young entrepreneurs from our institute invent their way out of regular work life and convert their ideas into reality.

As we start with a new academic year, the team of E-cell invites you all to its fun-filled Introductory Session where we will make you familiar with the structure and workings of E-cell and also the entrepreneurial environment here.

We aim to remove stereotypes from the mind of young entrepreneurs through this session. The session is going to be an evening full of learning new stuff while taking a glance at entrepreneurship, finance, etc, and also remembering the old legacies of our prestigious cell.

1/26/23, 11:41 PM - +91 95101 02170: Dear IIT Jodhpur Students, 

*Finlatics* in collaboration with *Prometeo*, is pleased to state that applications for the *Finlatics Financial Analyst Program* an *Online Live Project* that helps students gain *Work Experience* in *Equity Markets* and *Investment Banking* are now open. 
 
For this *Live Project*, students have the option to pick from *any one* of the three routes:
Route 1 - only Financial Markets
Route 2 - only Investment Banking
Route 3 - Financial Markets and Investment Banking

The program ends with a *Certificate of Work Experience* and a *Letter of Recommendation* and is doable *flexibly, from home*. 

To apply, you can fill out the form below and we'll get in touch:

https://www.finlatics.com/pevc_combo/application/index.php?utm_src=iitjo23w

The project is running across *leading campuses* including *IIT Bombay, IIT Kanpur, IIT Delhi and BITS Pilani* among others.

*No pre-requisites* or prior domain knowledge is required to be a part of the project.

*Project Duration*: 2 months

*Project Start*: Flexible on student choice

Students can also take a *break* on the project for any commitment and can take an *extension* on it, in case they cannot finish it within 2 months.

*Time commitment*: 4-5 hrs per week

If selected, the minimum induction fee for the program is:
Rs. 1499 + GST (only Financial Markets)
Rs. 1499 + GST (only Investment Banking)
Rs. 2199 + GST (Financial Markets and Investment Banking)

Applications are *common* for all routes and can be done from the *link* above. Applying from the link will take *2-3 mins* of your time and is free of any charges. 

Best regards,
Team Finlatics
Know more about us: https://www.finlatics.com/
Visit us on Linkedin: https://www.linkedin.com/company/fincrux-enabling-insights/

2/3/23, 6:03 PM - Parth Darshan Iitj: Dear, All,

Greetings from the Society of Alumni Affairs!

We are reaching out to you to invite nominations for the Society of Alumni Affairs. The Society of Alumni Affairs serves as a bridge between the institute and its alumni, working towards fostering a strong relationship between the two.

We are looking for dynamic and enthusiastic students who are passionate about contributing to their alma mater and working towards creating a lifelong connection with IIT Jodhpur. The selected students will have the opportunity to interact with alumni, attend events, and play a crucial role in the development of the institute.

Once again, We warmly welcome all students to join us on board in our journey in building Alumni relations for the welfare of IITJ Students.

We look forward to your active participation and support in this initiative. If you have any questions, please do not hesitate to reach out to us.
To apply for membership in the society.

https://docs.google.com/forms/d/e/1FAIpQLSfGGzG9F2zEKJA0fXnfPInfczpQ8ha0Y3JyS16LlE4p565jgQ/viewform

 The form will remain open till 11.59PM, 7th February.

Hoping to see an enthusiastic response from everyone :)

Thanks & Regards
Anirudh Bajaj
Vice President
Society of Alumni Affairs
IIT Jodhpur

3/17/23, 12:10 PM - +91 93684 23294: Three major student bodies – 
1. Student Senate – acts like a bridge between the student community and the administration.
2. Academic & Co-curricular Activity Council (ACAC) – 
3. Student Activity Council (SAC) – 
The ACAC & SAC help in empowering students in academic, social and cultural way.

SAC (Student Activity Council) – 
GEN SECY – ARJUN HURKET
1. Focus on student life and activities
2. Ensure coordination between General Student Body & administration
3. Extracurricular activities, hostel life & overall wellbeing
Boards under SAC & VPs- 
1. Board of Hostel Affairs (BHA) – Prabal Singh
2. Board of Art & Culture (BAC) – Devansh Menaria
3. Board of Student Sports (BSS) - Abhay Pratap Singh
4. Board of Literary Affairs (BLA) – Ved Prakash
5. Board of Student Welfare (BSW) – Abhinav Kashyap

Academic and Co-curricular Activity Council – 
GEN SECY – Manav Kapoor
1. Represent student body at academic and co-curricular platforms
2. Help in concerns about academic programs , teaching-learning
3. Promote innovation & entrepreneurship
4. Provide facilities for Non graded courses
Boards under ACAC
1. Board of Academic Interaction (BAI) – Aryan Tiwari
2. Board of Co-Curricular Affairs (BCCA) – Udit Agrawal
3. Board of Departmental Societies (BDS) – Mukul Bhele
4. Board of Innovation and Entrepreneurship (BIE) – Mitharth Arora
5. Board of Career Development (BCD) – Jeevesh Jain
6. Society for Alumni Affairs (SSA) – Anirudh Bajaj


Student Senate
Gen secy – Aman Prakash
1. Direct point of contact in case of issues faced by students
2. Representation of the Student Body as a whole
3. Work with councils to address concerns of the students
4. Bridge between the students and the administration

Student Gymkhana (Student Body at Institute Level)
A body organised by the student community of IITJ  for the welfare of the student community 
It has different societies such as Student Sports & Games Society, Cultural & Literary society, Design & Arts society, Science & Technology Society.
It includes – Captains of clubs & Hostel Secretaries and student elected representatives
Broadly 3 verticals – 
1. Student Societies
2. Student Campus Life
3. Student Representations

We hope this message finds you in good health and high spirits. We are pleased to announce the introductory session of the Rotaract Club of IIT Jodhpur, and we cordially invite you to join us for this event. Rotaract Club is a platform dedicated to community service, leadership development, and fostering a spirit of goodwill among our students. It provides an excellent opportunity for you to make a positive impact on society, develop your leadership skills, and network with like-minded individuals who share a passion for community service.

Here are the details of the introductory session:
Date: 2nd September,2023 (Saturday)
Time: 7:00 p.m.–8:00 p.m.
Venue: LHC 308

We encourage all students, regardless of their field of study or background, to attend this introductory session. Your participation and enthusiasm are essential in shaping the future of the Rotaract Club at IIT Jodhpur. We look forward to your presence at the introductory session and to embarking on this rewarding journey of service and leadership together.

“The best way to find yourself is to lose yourself in the service of others." - Mahatma Gandhi

Thanks and Regards,
Team, Rotaract Club of IIT Jodhpur

Flexibility:

10/23/23, 3:42 PM - +91 91680 05620: Dear fellow students,
We hope this message finds you well! We are excited to invite you to participate in a unique study that explores whether humans can distinguish between code written by humans and code generated by Large Language Models (LLMs). This is part of a project currently being run under Dr. Akshay Agarwal, Assistant Professor at IISER Bhopal. Your input is invaluable, and we believe you might enjoy this engaging survey.
 
*Study Details:*
*Objective:* Can humans distinguish between human-written and AI-generated code?
*Duration:* Approximately 20 minutes.
*Link to Survey:* https://forms.gle/1qcn3bp3LWqtUhjP9

*Why You Should Participate:*
*Contribute to Research:* Your participation will directly contribute to scientific research, helping us gain valuable insights into the capabilities of AI in code generation.
*Engaging Challenge:* This survey presents a fun and intriguing challenge for those interested in coding and artificial intelligence.
*Expand Your Knowledge:* You'll get a chance to explore and analyze code snippets, enhancing your coding skills and comprehension.
*Be a Part of Something Bigger:* By participating in this survey, you can contribute to advancing our understanding of AI's role in programming.

Thank you in advance for your time and contribution to this exciting research endeavour! We look forward to your participation and the valuable insights you will provide.

Best regards,
Aryaman A. Dixit
Yashaswini Mathur
Indian Institute of Science Education and Research Bhopal

12/7/23, 8:58 PM - Aditya Rathor Iitj: Hey everyone,

We are delighted to extend an invitation to an insightful interaction session featuring distinguished researchers in the field of 3D Computer Vision, Astitva Srivastava and Amogh Tiwari, from the Center for Visual Information Technology (CVIT) at IIIT Hyderabad.

Astitva and Amogh will generously share their academic journey, research accomplishments, and future aspirations. This session provides a unique opportunity for you to gain valuable insights into the field of 3D Computer Vision and the trajectory of successful research careers.

*Astitva Srivastava* is a dynamic and accomplished individual in Computer Vision and AI, currently a Google Ph.D. Fellow and 3D Vision Researcher at CVIT, IIIT Hyderabad. He is a recipient of the Qualcomm Innovation Fellowship India'23 and the TCS Research Fellowship'23, with expertise in Digital Clothed Human Avatars, 3D Virtual Try-on, Generative AI, and Large Language Models.
His publications focus on topics such as text-guided generation of 3D head models, shape-aware reconstruction of people in loose clothing, and 3D garment digitization for virtual try-on systems.
Please find his profile at - https://sarcastitva.me/

*Amogh Tiwari* is a dedicated dual-degree student, pursuing both a B.Tech and an M.S. (by Research) in Computer Science at the Center for Visual Information Technology (CVIT), IIIT Hyderabad. Under the guidance of Prof. Avinash Sharma, he is actively involved in groundbreaking research in the field of 3D Computer Vision.
Amogh's primary focus revolves around unraveling the complexities of understanding human interactions in three-dimensional space from images and videos.
Please find his profile at - https://amoghtiwari.github.io/

If you've ever wondered about diving into the world of research or just want some major inspiration for your own journey, this is the place to be!

Time: *7 December, 9:00 PM*
Venue: *CSE Department, 101*

We look forward to your participation in this enriching session.
